OL,3,C'Severe disruption' expected as 600
OL,4,Cbus drivers walk out over pay
OL,6,FDoug Claringbold, Managing Director
OL,7,Ffor First Bus in the West of England,
OL,8,Fsaid: "We are pleased to hear that our
OL,9,FBadgerline colleagues have voted to
OL,10,Faccept our full and final pay offer,
OL,11,Fwhich has resulted in them calling off
OL,12,Ftheir planned strikes and helped
OL,13,Freduce disruption to customers.
OL,15,F"However, we are disappointed to be
OL,16,Ftold that our Citylines colleagues
OL,17,Fhave rejected the pay offer, and
OL,18,Ftherefore their planned strikes for
OL,19,Ffour days from Tuesday 16th to Friday
OL,20,F19th September inclusive will go ahead.
